<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 23 at 5:21PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Brief wintry mix to fall during the evening commute ...
A brief mix of snow, sleet, and rain will impact the evening
commute through 7 PM EDT. The duration of precipitation at any one
location is expected to be brief, but will be long enough to make
the roadways wet. Air temperatures have risen into the middle to
upper 30s across Metro Detroit so widespread icy conditions are
not anticipated. However, isolated slippery conditions may exist
this evening particularly on bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.</description>
